148
00:08:52,430 --> 00:08:53,220
Hm...

149
00:08:53,220 --> 00:08:55,970
Next to the novel calzone we just had,

150
00:08:56,390 --> 00:08:58,850
this doesn't look very promisingâ€”

151
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:02,060
<i>Wh-What?!</i>

152
00:09:02,060 --> 00:09:03,850
<i>What is this rich depth of flavor?</i>

153
00:09:03,850 --> 00:09:06,810
<i>It has struck me to the very core of my being!</i>

154
00:09:07,150 --> 00:09:09,500
<i>The stock was made from beef flank and chicken</i>

155
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:12,070
<i>and seasoned with fennel and green cardamom.</i>

156
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:15,490
<i>The curry sauce tickles one's
nostrils in a delightful manner!</i>

157
00:09:15,490 --> 00:09:18,120
<i>It coats the thick noodles well!</i>

158
00:09:18,490 --> 00:09:19,370
What?!

159
00:09:19,370 --> 00:09:21,580
The secret ingredient is soy sauce?

160
00:09:21,580 --> 00:09:22,120
No.

161
00:09:22,450 --> 00:09:23,950
It's tamari soy sauce.

162
00:09:24,460 --> 00:09:27,600
It's manufactured primarily in the Tokai region.

163
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:30,340
It has a more concentrated
 umami than regular soy sauce,

164
00:09:30,340 --> 00:09:33,010
while still retaining a sweet, mellow flavor.

165
00:09:33,340 --> 00:09:36,930
