250
00:13:54,270 --> 00:13:57,630
The veterans of gourmet are all tongue-tied.

251
00:13:57,630 --> 00:14:00,860
Does that mean that dish is beyond even their comprehension?

252
00:14:00,860 --> 00:14:05,440
The curry sauce is foamy and ever so slightly warm.

253
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:08,160
It melts in your mouth.

254
00:14:09,140 --> 00:14:12,700
The tomato mousse is c-cold, and...

255
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:13,830
After I added the spices,

256
00:14:14,160 --> 00:14:16,870
I solidified it with sodium alginate.

257
00:14:16,870 --> 00:14:17,540
Huh?

258
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:22,670
Before you is a frozen mousse made from turmeric and powdered foie gras.

259
00:14:22,670 --> 00:14:26,920
The white object in the center is a puree of potatoes and six types of cheese.

260
00:14:26,920 --> 00:14:29,300
Its ingredients have been flash-frozen,

261
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:31,680
so it will melt in your mouth.

262
00:14:31,680 --> 00:14:35,770
Once you feel its coldness inside your mouth, enjoy the flaky pie crust.

263
00:14:35,770 --> 00:14:38,690
Flavored with coriander and other spices,

264
00:14:38,690 --> 00:14:40,400
the pie crust will cleanse your palate.

265
00:14:40,730 --> 00:14:42,180
"Thermal sense."

266
00:14:43,410 --> 00:14:46,400
It's one of the themes of molecular gastronomy:

267
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:48,880
a dish composed of different elements at contrasting temperatures.

268
00:14:48,880 --> 00:14:51,570
This dish embodies that theme.

269
00:14:51,570 --> 00:14:55,790
S-So, then... does it taste good?

270
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:57,580
Of course it's delicious!

271
00:14:57,580 --> 00:15:04,000
But I don't have the words to express how delicious it is in full!

272
00:15:04,340 --> 00:15:06,960
Not even a gifted writer can describe how it tastes?

273
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:08,800
With spices at its core,

274
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:11,470
this dish manipulates texture and
 temperature and makes them shine.

275
00:15:11,470 --> 00:15:14,930
It revolutionizes the entire field of cooking!

276
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:17,430
Indeed, if I were to give her a title,

277
00:15:18,980 --> 00:15:21,020
she would be a Global Innovator!

278
00:15:23,560 --> 00:15:25,610
N-Ninety-five points?!

279
00:15:26,150 --> 00:15:31,030
Nakiri Alice has received the highest
number of points and is now in the lead!

280
00:15:31,030 --> 00:15:33,120
Oh, not 100 points?

281
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:35,040
How unexpected.

282
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:35,740
But, I suppose...

283
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:38,890
Look, I received higher marks than Secretary-chan.

284
00:15:38,890 --> 00:15:40,500
Wh-Who are you calling Secretary-chan?!

285
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:41,760
Wow!

286
00:15:41,760 --> 00:15:44,170
Every judge gave her 19 points!

287
00:15:44,170 --> 00:15:45,500
That's almost a perfect score!

288
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:48,750
I can't believe those gourmands would do that.

289
00:15:48,760 --> 00:15:50,670
I haven't seen such a high score in a long time.

290
00:15:51,090 --> 00:15:53,580
Candidate Nakiri Alice is in first place,

291
00:15:53,580 --> 00:15:56,810
followed by Candidate Arato,
 then Candidate Takumi.

292
00:15:56,810 --> 00:16:00,430
Candidates Houjou and Isami
 are tied for fourth place!

293
00:16:00,680 --> 00:16:03,900
Only four may advance from
Group B to the main tournament!

294
00:16:04,350 --> 00:16:06,230
It's time for the judges to decide,

295
00:16:06,230 --> 00:16:08,070
"Who will advance to the main tournament?"

296
00:16:09,530 --> 00:16:10,440
Well!

297
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:13,530
That dish was quite interesting,
and certainly made for a fitting end!

298
00:16:13,780 --> 00:16:14,490
Indeed.

299
00:16:14,490 --> 00:16:16,800
Adjudicating the top dishes was a difficult task.

300
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:18,870
As usual, this year was a close contest.

301
00:16:18,870 --> 00:16:20,830
And on that note, let's proceed with the voting.

302
00:16:20,830 --> 00:16:22,160
Excuse me...

303
00:16:23,340 --> 00:16:27,420
M-My curry... is still waiting.

304
00:16:27,690 --> 00:16:29,210
<i>She's the one who butchered the monkfish.</i>

305
00:16:31,760 --> 00:16:32,510
Huh?

306
00:16:32,510 --> 00:16:33,630
She was still here?

307
00:16:35,220 --> 00:16:38,720
<i>Ugh, and here we were all
 revved up for the finale.</i>

308
00:16:39,770 --> 00:16:40,830
I'm sorry!

309
00:16:40,830 --> 00:16:41,730
So sorry!

310
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:44,560
Here it comes!

311
00:16:44,560 --> 00:16:46,440
It's Megumi's turn!

312
00:16:47,190 --> 00:16:50,230
Megumi!

313
00:16:50,610 --> 00:16:51,770
Everyone?

314
00:16:51,770 --> 00:16:53,260
What'cha doin' here?

315
00:16:53,260 --> 00:16:55,610
We left fishin' to the young 'uns today.

316
00:16:56,070 --> 00:16:58,700
We wanted to see you up on the big stage!

317
00:16:58,950 --> 00:17:01,160
O-Oh, ya shouldn't have.

318
00:17:01,450 --> 00:17:05,050
Hey, I guess those scary guys really like her.

319
00:17:05,050 --> 00:17:07,380
Who is Tadokoro Megumi, really?

320
00:17:08,840 --> 00:17:12,080
All right, Candidate Tadokoro,
 hurry up and come forward.

321
00:17:12,080 --> 00:17:12,920
Oh!

322
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:14,270
Go on, Megumi!

323
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:16,300
Show 'em what ya got!

324
00:17:16,300 --> 00:17:19,210
Yeah!

325
00:17:19,210 --> 00:17:20,100
Okay!

326
00:17:20,350 --> 00:17:22,060
<i>P-Please teach me!</i>

327
00:17:22,060 --> 00:17:23,770
<i>I want to help at home!</i>

328
00:17:24,310 --> 00:17:25,600
<i>Please!</i>

329
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:26,690
<i>I'm begging you!</i>

330
00:17:37,700 --> 00:17:40,410
It's monkfish dobu-jiru curry!

331
00:17:40,700 --> 00:17:41,980
Dobu-jiru...

332
00:17:41,980 --> 00:17:44,370
That's a hot pot dish with monkfish as the main ingredient, no?

333
00:17:44,620 --> 00:17:45,540
Correct.

334
00:17:45,540 --> 00:17:49,840
It's a dish that has been passed down by fishermen
 of the Ibaraki and Fukushima prefectures for generations.

335
00:17:50,140 --> 00:17:52,000
<i>Monkfish in curry?</i>

336
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,880
<i>Just what is she thinking?</i>

337
00:17:55,090 --> 00:17:56,800
Whew...

338
00:17:56,800 --> 00:18:02,090
I see. So this is why you used monkfish.

339
00:18:02,090 --> 00:18:07,600
The main characteristic of dobu-jiru hot pot is that 
monkfish liver is sauteed and rendered into a paste.

340
00:18:08,040 --> 00:18:12,610
Miso and sake are added to the liver to form the base of the broth.

341
00:18:13,100 --> 00:18:15,530
However, this girl also added spices to that mix,

342
00:18:15,530 --> 00:18:17,780
effectively creating a liver curry miso paste.

343
00:18:18,040 --> 00:18:21,280
The deliciousness just seeps
 into you. How addictive!

344
00:18:21,620 --> 00:18:25,790
The unctuous, deep flavor of the liver is
 a surprisingly good complement to the spices!

345
00:18:26,250 --> 00:18:28,330
Still, I must say,

346
00:18:28,330 --> 00:18:31,340
after the previous dish, it's all the more apparent to me that...

347
00:18:31,340 --> 00:18:32,210
How should I put it?

348
00:18:32,460 --> 00:18:34,710
It's a very <i>human</i> dish.

349
00:18:35,010 --> 00:18:39,300
The ingredients are monkfish meat, skin, fin, and...

350
00:18:39,300 --> 00:18:39,840
Hm?

351
00:18:41,390 --> 00:18:45,520
Kogiku kabocha squash, Tachikawa burdock root, and Akasuji daikon!

352
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:47,480
Y-Yes!

353
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:49,980
They're all ingredients that
 are local to my hometown.

354
00:18:50,380 --> 00:18:53,980
I wanted to highlight their strengths,
 so I've been experimenting a lot.

355
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:56,490
Curry is very assertive,

356
00:18:56,900 --> 00:19:00,740
so it was hard to blend it with the sweetness and bitterness of other vegetables.

357
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:06,330
But I realized I could use dobu-jiru with 
monkfish liver to take advantage of the spices.

358
00:19:06,330 --> 00:19:10,080
The broth could then bridge the gap between them and the flavor of the vegetables.

359
00:19:10,080 --> 00:19:11,830
I wanted to make the kind of curry

360
00:19:12,130 --> 00:19:16,670
where you can almost experience
 how it feels to be in my hometown!

361
00:19:17,550 --> 00:19:17,960
<i>What?</i>

362
00:19:18,510 --> 00:19:20,510
<i>Megumi really made this?</i>

363
00:19:20,510 --> 00:19:21,090
<i>Yes!</i>

364
00:19:21,090 --> 00:19:23,990
<i>No one here can beat her at cooking any more!</i>

365
00:19:26,010 --> 00:19:30,060
<i>I've heard that there's a famous
 culinary school in Tokyo.</i>

366
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:32,520
<i>Would you like to go?</i>

367
00:19:32,520 --> 00:19:33,190
<i>What?</i>

368
00:19:33,560 --> 00:19:37,100
<i>I hear many of their graduates go on to awe the world.</i>

369
00:19:37,100 --> 00:19:42,780
<i>B-But Mom, I want to help out at this inn when I'm done with school.</i>

370
00:19:42,780 --> 00:19:47,910
<i>If that's your final decision, that's fine.</i>

371
00:19:47,910 --> 00:19:49,250
<i>I'd be happy to have you here.</i>

372
00:19:49,870 --> 00:19:53,820
<i>But before you make that choice,</i>

373
00:19:53,820 --> 00:19:56,780
<i>I want you to catch a glimpse
 of a bigger world, at least once.</i>

374
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:00,050
What?!

375
00:20:00,050 --> 00:20:02,910
How can Megumi's dish only score in the teens?!

376
00:20:02,910 --> 00:20:03,930
I told ya already!

377
00:20:03,930 --> 00:20:07,500
The five judges' scores all add 
up to a hundred, old man!

378
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:08,560
Good job!

379
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:10,310
That's our Megumi!

380
00:20:14,560 --> 00:20:17,070
<i>Here, a good luck charm to help you stay focused on your studies.</i>

381
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:20,070
<i>Tokyo, huh?</i>

382
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:23,160
<i>It'll get lonely around here.</i>

383
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:27,080
<i>However, we can't let Megumi's talent go to waste.</i>

384
00:20:27,390 --> 00:20:29,540
<i>Good luck, Megumi!</i>

385
00:20:29,870 --> 00:20:34,250
<i>Megumi might become the biggest fish to come outta these parts!</i>

386
00:20:37,630 --> 00:20:38,670
<i>Megumi...</i>

387
00:20:38,670 --> 00:20:40,090
<i>How's school?</i>

388
00:20:40,090 --> 00:20:42,500
<i>Mom, um...</i>

389
00:20:44,050 --> 00:20:45,470
<i>It's going fine.</i>

390
00:20:45,470 --> 00:20:47,430
<i>I'm having a lot of fun in my classes!</i>

391
00:20:48,470 --> 00:20:51,440
<i>Megumi, you're pretty amazing, y'know?</i>

392
00:20:51,440 --> 00:20:54,110
<i>Do you want to come practice cooking again?</i>

393
00:20:54,110 --> 00:20:55,920
<i>We'll keep you company.</i>

394
00:20:55,920 --> 00:20:57,110
<i>Oh, it's okay!</i>

395
00:20:57,110 --> 00:20:58,150
<i>Thanks for the offer.</i>

396
00:20:58,440 --> 00:21:01,610
<i>But I think I'll practice on my own today.</i>

397
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:20,130
Your time's finally come, Tadokoro-chan.

398
00:21:21,210 --> 00:21:23,620
It's time for you to leave the
 tiny world you started off in...

399
00:21:25,120 --> 00:21:26,420
and soar into the sky.

400
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:30,840
Candidate Tadokoro Megumi has 88 points!

401
00:21:30,840 --> 00:21:31,960
She's in fourth place!

402
00:21:31,960 --> 00:21:34,220
She passed the preliminaries!

403
00:21:36,560 --> 00:21:39,230
Houjou Miyoko didn't make it
 out of the preliminaries!

404
00:21:39,230 --> 00:21:40,150
This is a major upset!

405
00:21:40,150 --> 00:21:42,730
Megumi! You did it!

406
00:21:42,980 --> 00:21:45,700
Megumi!

407
00:21:45,700 --> 00:21:47,840
Megumi!

408
00:21:47,840 --> 00:21:49,950
Megumi!

409
00:21:49,950 --> 00:21:51,780
Megumi!

410
00:21:53,500 --> 00:21:56,500
<i>I thought I'd have to overpower the men to succeed.</i>

411
00:21:57,290 --> 00:21:58,580
<i>But with the way I am now...</i>

412
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:00,760
<i>is that just a pipe dream?</i>

413
00:23:37,010 --> 00:23:38,310
Okay, this is no good at all.

414
00:23:38,640 --> 00:23:41,270
How could I possibly score a dish like this?

415
00:23:41,270 --> 00:23:45,360
U-Um, wh-what is the score?

416
00:23:45,360 --> 00:23:47,020
Didn't you hear me the first time?

417
00:23:47,020 --> 00:23:48,320
I said it's no good.

418
00:23:49,470 --> 00:23:53,950
Th-The total is 19 points.

419
00:23:54,990 --> 00:23:58,370
Sendawara Natsume keeps awarding zero points to each dish.

420
00:23:58,370 --> 00:24:00,750
She's already judged more than ten candidates,

421
00:24:00,750 --> 00:24:02,910
and she's yet to give even a single point.

422
00:24:02,910 --> 00:24:05,250
All the dishes looked pretty good too.

423
00:24:05,250 --> 00:24:07,800
Wh-What the hell's going on here?

424
00:24:08,120 --> 00:24:10,920
Maybe the judges for Group A
 are way more strict.

425
00:24:10,920 --> 00:24:15,260
V-Very well, n-next up is
 Candidate Kurokiba Ryou!

426
00:24:15,260 --> 00:24:17,040
Come on up, please!

427
00:24:24,980 --> 00:24:27,000
Next time on <i>Shokugeki no Souma</i>,

428
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:28,410
the twenty-third dish.

429
00:24:28,410 --> 00:24:30,540
Ryou-kun, say something already!

430
00:24:31,900 --> 00:24:33,950
The Competition of the Blossoming Individuals.

431
00:24:34,570 --> 00:24:36,910
I will be the one at the top!

432
00:24:36,910 --> 00:24:38,760
Isn't that a bit much?

433
00:24:38,760 --> 00:24:39,850
No way.

434
00:24:39,850 --> 00:24:41,910
It's how these things go.

